<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-09-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-09-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="558" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d558">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/218: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-11T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 11,
                                        1925—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>241. Your 389, September 10, 5 p.m. You may inform British Chargé that
                            assurance is satisfactory, and that you are ready to proceed with
                            negotiations with Chinese Government regarding Shanghai incident.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>